<%- include('../partials/header', { title: title }) %>

<div class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="legal-header">
            <h1>Community Guidelines</h1>
            <p class="last-updated">Last updated: December 2024</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-content">
            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>Welcome to the Sayonika Community!</h2>
                <p>
                    Sayonika is a community-driven platform for sharing and discovering DDLC mods. These guidelines help ensure 
                    our community remains welcoming, creative, and respectful for all members. By participating in our community, 
                    you agree to follow these guidelines.
                </p>
                <div class="legal-highlight info">
                    <p>
                        <strong>Remember:</strong> We're all here because we love DDLC and want to share amazing mods with each other. 
                        Let's keep the community positive and supportive!
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>1. Be Respectful and Kind</h2>
                <h3>1.1 Treat Everyone with Respect</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Be courteous and considerate in all interactions</li>
                    <li>Respect different opinions, playstyles, and creative choices</li>
                    <li>Use constructive language when providing feedback</li>
                    <li>Remember there's a real person behind every username</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>1.2 No Harassment or Bullying</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Personal attacks, insults, or harassment will not be tolerated</li>
                    <li>Don't target users based on their identity, background, or beliefs</li>
                    <li>Avoid inflammatory or deliberately provocative comments</li>
                    <li>Report harassment to moderators rather than engaging</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>1.3 Keep Discussions Civil</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Disagree respectfully and focus on ideas, not individuals</li>
                    <li>Avoid excessive profanity or offensive language</li>
                    <li>Stay on topic in discussions and comments</li>
                    <li>Don't spam or flood comment sections</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>2. Content Guidelines</h2>
                <h3>2.1 Mod Content Standards</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Original Work:</strong> Only upload mods you created or have permission to share</li>
                    <li><strong>Quality Control:</strong> Test your mods before uploading to ensure they work properly</li>
                    <li><strong>Accurate Descriptions:</strong> Provide clear, honest descriptions of your mod's content</li>
                    <li><strong>Proper Tagging:</strong> Use appropriate tags and categories for discoverability</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>2.2 NSFW Content Policy</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Adult content is allowed but must be clearly marked as NSFW</li>
                    <li>Include content warnings for sensitive topics (violence, mental health themes, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Ensure NSFW content complies with applicable laws</li>
                    <li>Keep NSFW content out of thumbnails and preview images</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>2.3 Prohibited Content</h3>
                <p>The following types of content are not allowed:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Malicious software, viruses, or harmful code</li>
                    <li>Content that violates copyright or intellectual property rights</li>
                    <li>Illegal content or content promoting illegal activities</li>
                    <li>Hate speech, discrimination, or content targeting specific groups</li>
                    <li>Excessive gore or disturbing content without proper warnings</li>
                    <li>Content that violates Team Salvato's IP Guidelines</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>3. Community Participation</h2>
                <h3>3.1 Constructive Feedback</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Provide helpful, specific feedback when reviewing mods</li>
                    <li>Balance criticism with positive observations</li>
                    <li>Suggest improvements rather than just pointing out problems</li>
                    <li>Acknowledge the effort creators put into their work</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>3.2 Supporting Creators</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Leave thoughtful reviews and ratings</li>
                    <li>Share mods you enjoy with others</li>
                    <li>Report bugs or issues constructively</li>
                    <li>Respect creators' time and creative decisions</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>3.3 Community Events and Discussions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Participate positively in community events and challenges</li>
                    <li>Share knowledge and help newcomers</li>
                    <li>Contribute to discussions about DDLC and modding</li>
                    <li>Promote collaboration and community building</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>4. Technical Guidelines</h2>
                <h3>4.1 Mod Quality Standards</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ensure mods are compatible with the base DDLC game</li>
                    <li>Include clear installation instructions</li>
                    <li>Provide system requirements if applicable</li>
                    <li>Test mods thoroughly before release</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>4.2 File Management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use appropriate file formats and compression</li>
                    <li>Keep file sizes reasonable when possible</li>
                    <li>Include necessary files and dependencies</li>
                    <li>Organize files clearly within archives</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>4.3 Updates and Maintenance</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Update mod descriptions if content changes significantly</li>
                    <li>Respond to user reports of technical issues</li>
                    <li>Consider compatibility when updating mods</li>
                    <li>Archive or mark discontinued mods appropriately</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>5. Intellectual Property Respect</h2>
                <h3>5.1 DDLC IP Guidelines</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Follow Team Salvato's official IP Guidelines for DDLC</li>
                    <li>Don't distribute the base game files</li>
                    <li>Respect the original characters and setting</li>
                    <li>Include appropriate disclaimers about fan-made content</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>5.2 Third-Party Content</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Only use assets you have permission to use</li>
                    <li>Credit original creators of music, art, or other assets</li>
                    <li>Respect licenses and usage terms</li>
                    <li>When in doubt, create original content or ask for permission</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>6. Reporting and Moderation</h2>
                <h3>6.1 How to Report Issues</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use the report function for content that violates guidelines</li>
                    <li>Contact moderators for serious issues or harassment</li>
                    <li>Provide specific details when reporting problems</li>
                    <li>Don't abuse the reporting system</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>6.2 Moderation Process</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>All uploaded content is reviewed before publication</li>
                    <li>Violations may result in content removal or account restrictions</li>
                    <li>Serious or repeated violations may lead to permanent bans</li>
                    <li>Appeals can be made through official channels</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>6.3 Self-Moderation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review your own content before uploading</li>
                    <li>Edit or remove content if you realize it violates guidelines</li>
                    <li>Help maintain community standards through positive example</li>
                    <li>Encourage others to follow guidelines respectfully</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>7. Account Responsibility</h2>
                <h3>7.1 Account Security</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Keep your account credentials secure</li>
                    <li>Don't share your account with others</li>
                    <li>Report suspicious activity immediately</li>
                    <li>Use strong, unique passwords</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>7.2 Profile Guidelines</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use appropriate usernames and display names</li>
                    <li>Keep profile information accurate and appropriate</li>
                    <li>Use suitable profile pictures (no NSFW content)</li>
                    <li>Represent yourself honestly</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>8. Getting Help</h2>
                <p>If you need assistance or have questions about these guidelines:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Community Support:</strong> Ask other community members for help</li>
                    <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Check our help pages and FAQs</li>
                    <li><strong>Contact Moderators:</strong> Reach out through official channels</li>
                    <li><strong>Discord Community:</strong> Join our Discord server for real-time help</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="legal-highlight success">
                    <p>
                        <strong>New to modding?</strong> Don't worry! Our community is here to help. 
                        Feel free to ask questions and learn from experienced modders.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>9. Updates to Guidelines</h2>
                <p>
                    These guidelines may be updated periodically to reflect community needs and platform changes. 
                    Significant updates will be announced to the community. Continued use of Sayonika constitutes 
                    acceptance of any updated guidelines.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-footer">
            <p>
                <strong>Remember:</strong> These guidelines exist to keep our community welcoming and creative. 
                When in doubt, choose kindness and respect. Together, we can build an amazing space for DDLC mod creators and players!
            </p>
            <div class="legal-actions">
                <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Back to Home</a>
                <a href="/terms" class="btn btn-outline">Terms of Service</a>
                <a href="/privacy" class="btn btn-outline">Privacy Policy</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

